cc @caiconghui @morrySnow

> m with the rounding result, and the precision problem seems to have been fix

Currently, literal 16.025000 is considered as DECIMALV2 by default so we got a wrong result. To test DECIMALV3, you should:
1. CREATE TABLE with a DECIMALV3 column `col`
2. INSERT data INTO this table (e.g. 16.025000)
3. select round(`col`, 2) from this table;
